ailable in pure cashmere and mixed cashmere and silk with a range of warm colors which makes them perfect for any occasion.',NULL,'cn','2014-09-03 16:53:20','2014-09-03 16:53:20',NULL,1,'product',0,NULL),(20191,'WANDERER','The yak grows a thick woolen coat to survive the long winters of the Tibetan plains. In the warmth of spring, herders comb out the soft down, grade it, and use it to make the finest clothing. Yak wool is strong and dense and maintains its natural tone even when dyed. The SHANG XIA Wanderer collection is a combination of three tones of hand spun and hand dyed yarn, artfully woven to form this exclusive SHANG XIA fabric. Every Wanderer coat is carefully edged with fine calfskin. It took over 400 hours of painstaking attention to detail. Instead of the multiple panels of modern clothe-making, the Wanderer is based on Chinese traditional dress tailoring, so that the overcoats exude solidity and unity. They are form fitting, but comfortably roomy, like the long cadence of a herding song ringing out across the high plains.',NULL,'cn','2014-09-03 16:53:20','2014-09-03 16:53:20',NULL,1,'product',0,NULL),(20192,'CAREFREE','Woven from cashmere and cotton, this men’s collection is both soft and comfortable. \n\nWoven from beginning to end in one continuous thread, it is an outstanding technical achievement, evenly finished with no seams. Inspired by Han dynasty costumes, the simple line, color and cross over tie, are the model of confidence and nature of traditional Chinese elegance.',NULL,'cn','2014-09-03 16:53:21','2014-09-03 16:53:21',NULL,1,'product',0,NULL),(20193,'SCULPTURE ','Created by expertly skilled master craftsmen, using similar techniques to those used when hand-felting fabric for Mongolian yurts, these sculpted garments are made in felt. Inspired by traditional Han dynasty clothing, this collection reflects the traditional elegance of Chinese style.\nEach garment is unique and sculpted into a seamless shape to create a 3-dimensional garment in